narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Research for credit. If you are already researching in a lab might as well take it and get the credit.
Pretty standard. It's research for credit. At the end of the semester, you can either write a paper or do a presentation in front of your lab group.

This is an excellent way to get started on senior thesis research, requiring only a short project proposal, update, and a presentation/paper at the end. What you get out of it is largely what you put into it. I would recommend this course!
It's a great chance to get head started in your senior project
YES!! Pursue your own projects while you are in school. Never in your life would you get the chance to truly be the master of your research again unless you become a PI or entrepreneur.

Standard - research for credit class. Both Professor Staib and Professor Duncan are super relaxed so if you miss deadlines or whatever you won't really have to worry about being penalized, as long as you get your work done.
